definition.value: Note that this term refers to the mechanosensory hair cells of the inner ear.
Note that immunologists typically use the word 'development' to refer to cells of B or T cell lineages undergoing the process that GO describes as 'cell differentiation'.

Note that 'hydrolysis' is actually a reaction rather than a process. The synonym 'hemoglobin hydrolysis' was the text string associated with the secondary ID GO:0020029, which was retained because its definition did describe a process.
Note that an immunoglobulin complex has the function of antigen binding if a suitable antigen is available.
See also the cellular component term 'MHC class I peptide loading complex ; GO:0042824'.
